---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Card from "../components/Card.astro";
---

<Layout title="PixelSaver - Home" class="text-cyan-50">
  <main class="container mx-auto px-6 py-12 grid grid-cols-1 gap-4">
    <!-- 
    From- To is a gradient
    text-transparent and bg-clip-text is the thing to make it look from behind the text
    leading-snug fits the j, g, y, etc that comes out from below
    -->
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-bold mb-4 text-center
    from-pink-medium to-pink-light bg-radial-[at_50%_75%] text-transparent bg-clip-text 
    leading-snug
    ">
      Saving Pixels, one at a time!
    </h1>
    <p>
      I never would have guessed that I would be coding a website. I
      always found HTML and CSS to be too burdensome to get around to,
      but here I am, typing this into my laptop. Funny how the world
      works.
    </p>
    <div class="grid gap-2 grid-cols-[repeat(auto-fit,minmax(200px,1fr))]">
      <Card title="About Me" description="Just what you think it is" href="/Saving-Pixels/about" />
      <Card title="Links" description="Bookmarks for me!" href="/Saving-Pixels/links" />
      <Card title="Blank" description="" href="/Saving-Pixels/blank" />
      <Card title="Showoff" description="Things I'm trying out in Astro while learning" href="/Saving-Pixels/showoff" />
      <Card title="Readme" description="The github readme for this website!" href="/Saving-Pixels/readme" />
      <Card title="Palette" description="The color palette for this website" href="/Saving-Pixels/palette" />
      <Card title="Licensing" description="MIT License" href="/Saving-Pixels/license" />
    </div>
  </main>
</Layout>